title: Googles first quarter under Alphabet reveals revenue and profit growth but little else
text:
Google's first quarter under Alphabet reveals revenue and profit growth but little else 
Pocket Lint Friday 23rd October, 2015 
Google has just posted its third-quarter earnings. 
Actually, we should say Alphabet did. Although Google is now part of a larger holding compant called Alphabet, we still get to peek at Google's finances. Unfortunately, however, Google is currently hiding numbers for some of its businesses, including Google X and Life Sciences, but we did learn a bit about mobile search and advertising. 
Starting off with the general financial stuff...Alphabet reported revenue of $18.67 billion (a 13 per cent increase year over year) and a profit of $4.7 billion (a 27 per cent increase year over year). Th...
